The cited source states that "[Inayat] Khan claimed that “the God of the Sufi is the God of every creed, and the God of all. Names make no difference to him. Allah, God, Gott, Dieu, Khuda, Brahma, or Bhagwan, all these names and more are the names of his God; and yet to him God is beyond the limitation of name.”! " (cited source, p.181). Where did this "hulul" and "God dwells in some creatures" nonsense come from?
